<article>
    <h1>Garden de&#xAD;lights</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201017/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-17"><time>2020-10-17</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HOME AND GARDEN</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>This year, the Com­mu­nity Garden Fes­ti­val, which is usu­ally held in HortPark, takes on a mainly virtual for­mat on Oct 24 and 25.</p>
    <p>Here are high­lights of free pro­grammes – avail­able at NParks Face­book (www.face­book.com/ nparks­buzz) & NParks SG YouTube – de­signed to make gar­den­ing ac­ces­si­ble to ev­ery­one.</p>
    <p>OCT 24 2 to 3pm</p>
    <p>• Live chat with Com­mu­nity in Bloom gar­den­ers:</p>
    <p>Hear their ex­pe­ri­ences run­ning a com­mu­nity garden.</p>
    <p>• Tour of HortPark’s high­lights: Join a com­pre­hen­sive tour of HortPark for a be­hind-thescenes peek to gain ideas for your home garden.</p>
    <p>• Flo­ral ar­range­ment demon­stra­tion: Learn flo­ral ar­range­ment with a fun twist by us­ing fresh har­vest and botan­i­cal prod­ucts to cre­ate a flo­ral cen­tre­piece.</p>
    <p>• e-Mar­ket­place: An­swer quizzes through­out the show and stand to win vouch­ers and sign up for ex­clu­sive work­shop slots.</p>
    <p>3 to 4pm</p>
    <p>• Tour of Flo­ral Walk: Ex­plore and ad­mire the vi­brant fresh blooms and fo­liage that adorn the gate­way to HortPark.</p>
    <p>• Tour of Pasir Pan­jang Nurs­ery: Get a rare glimpse into NParks’ nurs­ery op­er­a­tions, which are crit­i­cal in the green­ing of Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>• Live chat with plant spe­cial­ists on soil types and prop­er­ties: Get tips from NParks’ plant health spe­cial­ists on pre­par­ing the per­fect soil mix at home by ex­plor­ing soil types and prop­er­ties.</p>
    <p>OCT 25 2 to 3pm</p>
    <p>• Tour of HortPark’s My Back­yard Kitchen: Ex­plore plants that can be grown in one’s back­yard or bal­cony space such as aro­matic herbs, spices and ed­i­ble flow­ers per­fect for tea-time spreads. • Live chat with al­lot­ment gar­den­ers: Hear from</p>
    <p>th­ese grow­ers about de­sign­ing al­lot­ment plots. • Culi­nary demon­stra­tion: Watch chefs from HortPark’s Vine­yard and Canopy restau­rants whip up dishes us­ing ed­i­bles sourced from a typ­i­cal home garden.</p>
    <p>3 to 4pm</p>
    <p>• Live chat with plant spe­cial­ists on manag­ing</p>
    <p>pests and fer­til­is­ing: Get tips on plant nutri­tion by ex­plor­ing dif­fer­ent nu­tri­ent types. NParks’ plant health spe­cial­ists will also fo­cus on po­ten­tial pests and diseases and how to avoid them.</p>
    <p>• Hy­dro­ponic demon­stra­tion with ComCrop: Ex­plore hy­dro­ponic tech­niques to en­joy a boun­ti­ful veg­etable har­vest in a small home. • e-Mar­ket­place: An­swer quizzes through­out the show and stand to win vouch­ers and sign up for ex­clu­sive work­shop slots.</p>


</article>

